CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier, April 12, 1958, pg. 3 reads: "Pan-Hellenic heads - Miss Eleanor Perry (left), was elected president, and Miss Dorothy Pridgen, vice president, of the Pan-Hellenic Council at the University of Pittsburgh. Miss Pridgen is the first of her race to hold such a high position in the university's council.  They are discussing the tri-semester plan proposed at Pitt. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Eleanor Perry and Dorothy Pridgen, president and vice president of Pan-Hellenic Council at University of Pittsburgh
